## 2) Commercial/Company Use License (Authorization Required)

Any Commercial Use requires **explicit written authorization** from the Licensor.

To request authorization, email:
- **sherlott@live.com**

When requesting, include (recommended):
- your name/company;
- intended use (internal tool, SaaS, embedded product, consulting, etc.);
- expected scale (users/tenants);
- whether you need redistribution rights.

Commercial terms (including fees, scope, redistribution rights, support, SLAs, and trademark/branding permissions) are defined only in the written authorization. Without that authorization, no commercial/company rights are granted.

### 2.0 Attribution still applies
Unless explicitly waived in writing by the Licensor, the Attribution requirements in §1.3 apply to Commercial Use as well. Commercial authorization does not grant permission to remove or hide credit.

### 2.1 Compensation and value sharing
Because the Project is intended to demonstrate the author’s expertise and may be used to create business value, Commercial authorization may require Compensation (e.g., a license fee, royalty/revenue share, sponsorship, or an agreed value exchange such as significant upstream contributions). The exact terms are negotiated by email and confirmed in writing.

The intent of this section is to prevent situations where organizations extract value from the Project without giving visible credit and/or fair value back to the author.

### 2.2 Partner-friendly intent (non-binding)
The Licensor may, at their sole discretion, grant Commercial authorization under favorable terms to organizations that provide meaningful improvements, bug fixes, security fixes, documentation, or other contributions that help the Project evolve.

